</P>
<P>
   KEYBOARD-CONVERSATIONS (New York) _ In classical music, it often
seems, all roads lead to Beethoven. Two such paths converged last
week when Jeffrey Siegel and Ruth Laredo, pianists and
commentators, turned their efforts to that German master. By James
R. Oestreich.
</P>
