<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIVE-WALKER-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story WALKER-COLUMN
(k) by ADRIAN-WALKER, which moved Jan. 8, will wish to use the
following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A Boston Globe column by Adrian Walker stated incorrectly that
former Senate President William M. Bulger was among a number of
legislators fined in 1992 by the Massachusetts Ethics Commission,
and that the commission's budget was then promptly cut. Bulger has
never been fined by the Commission. Fourteen past and present
legislators were fined as a result of activities in 1992, but the
fines were imposed in 1994 and 1995. Although the House attempted
to cut the commission's budget in 1995, the Senate, then headed by
Bulger, resisted the cut. The funding was restored by a
House-Senate conference committee.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
