   Broadcast.com would be a textbook example of the new Internet
businesses, if a textbook existed. It was founded almost four years
ago by Todd Wagner and Mark Cuban, old college friends who were
then in their mid-30s. When it went public last year, it had one of
the fastest opening-day sprints in Wall Street history, rising
nearly 250 percent.
