   TECH-REPORT _ Tech briefs on new products and developments. This
week: Maptech, a National Park Digital Guide. (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   POWERUSER-COLUMN _ A regular series of columns for advanced
computer users. This week: enhancing gaming experiences. (Yandel,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   CORD-BLOOD-BANKS _ ATLANTA _ When Barbara Marston of Atlanta has
her first baby she'd like to make a gift of the cord blood to help
children nationwide in need of a bone marrow transplant. But she
can't because no such public cord blood collection exists in
Atlanta, or anywhere in Georgia. At least not yet. Emory University
is considering starting such a program, perhaps within a year. But
until then, mothers-to-be such as Marston are left to sort through
brochures of private companies making the pitch to buy biological
insurance. These companies collect and save the mother's placenta
and umblical blood and store it for a fee. (Guthrie, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   w/PLACENTA _ Most hospitals throw out the afterbirth, but some
cultures revere the placenta for its symbolism of life, spirit and
individuality. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
