<HEADLINE>
`OUT OF SIGHT' SIZZLES; `TRUMAN SHOW' OBVIOUS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Out of Sight'' _ George Clooney and Jennifer
Lopez sizzle in this crime melodrama directed by Steven Soderbergh
and costarring Don Cheadle, Ving Rhames, and a remarkable Albert
Brooks. Both the National Society and Boston Society of Film
Critics voted this as the Best Picture of 1998.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Truman Show'' _ Jim Carrey's rubbery performance as the
ultimate TV star goes a long way toward assuring this satiric
comedy's success. The problem is that virtually every movie fan
knows the premise _ Carrey lives his whole life in a TV show
without knowing it _ so there is no real sense of discovery.
</P>
<P>
   ``p'' _ Darren Aronofsky directs this low-budget film with great
imagination. Shot in eerie black-and-white, it merges the suspense
thriller with mathematical probabilities and comes up with a
winning formula, without being formulaic. Sean Gullette's
performance, as the mathematics genius, deserves Oscar
consideration.
</P>
<P>
   ``Henry Fool'' _ Independent film favorite Hal Hartley, whose
previous films include ``Flirt'' and ``Amateur,'' directs James
Urbaniak in this dark family comedy. It wears its art on its sleeve
but, nevertheless, it has some wonderful moments. Where else are
you going to find an introspective garbage collector in a movie?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   On Feb. 2, Kino on Video will release three more terrific titles
in their ``Film Noir: The Dark Side of Hollywood'' series. A
digitally remastered version of Jules Dassin's ``The Naked City''
(1948's inspiration for both of the TV series), joins his other
classic, ``Brute Force'' (1947), with Burt Lancaster, and Fritz
Lang's ``The Blue Gardenia'' (1953).
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Jan. 19: ``Smoke Signals,'' ``Invasion
Earth,'' ``Because of Him,'' ``The Amazing Mrs. Holliday,'' ``Slums
of Beverly Hills,'' ``Evidence of Blood,'' ``Buffalo Island,''
``Little City,'' ``Buffalo 66,'' ``Mafia!'' Jan. 26: ``Kurt and
Courtney,'' ``Whatever,'' ``Cube,'' ``Rush Hour.'' Feb. 2:
``There's Something About Mary,'' ``Mulan,'' ``The Alarmist,''
``Brute Force,'' ``Shooting Fish,'' ``Naked City,'' ``Heaven or
Vegas,'' ``The Blue Gardenia,'' ``John Carpenter's Vampires,''
``Who Am I?'' Feb. 9: ``Next Stop Wonderland,'' ``Rounders,''
``Office Killer,'' ``The Invasion Begins,'' ``A Merry War,''
``Legionnaire.'' Feb. 16: ``Snake Eyes,'' ``Beyond Silence,''
``Since You've Been Gone.'' Feb. 23: ``Carnival of Souls,'' ``Shame
II: The Secret.''
</P>
</TEXT>
