lawsuit. But there's a confidentiality agreement barring all sides
from talking, so we wont get details. Opening statements in a $6
million suit were delayed last week as lawyers on both sides
talked. Eleven people and corporations allege they paid at least
$10,000 for each of dozens of souvenir booths, supplies and
services, but received nothing in return. Defendants include
Creative Travel Services, which also brought 3,000 teen-agers from
around the country to work at the kiosks, but then could neither
feed nor house them. (Croft, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
