coronation occurred 18 months ago, when the House adjourned and
members immediately agreed that Speaker Pete Laney should get a
fourth term. Laney will be re-elected without opposition, despite
his pledge in 1993 to be a reform speaker who unlike his
predecessors would serve only one term. A look at the man and
office. (Greenberger, Austin American-Statesman).
