   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-CULT _ MEVASSARET ZION _ Other than the fact that they
were Americans and that there children were not in school, their
Israeli neighbors did not find anything unusual about the family
that moved into this Jerusalem suburb a few months ago. They were
friendly, asked a lot of questions about Israeli current events and
did the usual sightseeing. But, Israeli police raided this villa
and another in a nearby town this weekend, arresting eight adults
and four children believed to be in a Denver, Colo.-based Christian
millennium cult that planned to die in suicidal attacks at the end
of this year. Police said Monday that three members of the group
would be held while the rest are deported back to the United
States. Left on their yard, apparently discarded by police, was a
folder containing presentation notes that extolled prophecies of
Charles Manson and warnings of the ``impending judgment of the
United States.'' (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
</P>
