<P>
   ATTENTION FOOD AND FEATURE EDITORS &QL; 
 &QL; 
201-ADVISORY: The Arizona Republic's food! section starts its
Cooking 201 series this month, a follow-up to the popular Cooking
101 series that ran for 20 weeks from last January through May on
the basics of cooking. This year's series is different. The topics
will run once a month for 12 months.
</P>
<P>
   The series opens on Jan. 13 with 201-YEAST: Conquering the Yeast
Beast, by food writer Judy Walker. Each topic is a package of
stories with multiple slugs and photos.
</P>
<P>
   The next two packages are scheduled for Feb. 17, 201-DECORATE:
Cake Decorating, and Mar. 31, 201-BRUNCH: With waffle and egg
recipes suitable for Easter.
</P>
