<P>
   TV-SNITCH-REVIEW (Undated) _ Walter Goodman reviews ``Snitch,''
a 90-minute Frontline episode on PBS stations. Relying mainly on
horror stories of low-level drug suspects who are serving long
prison terms on evidence supplied by more culpable pals and
collaborators, the show makes a case that the war on drugs is being
perverted by incentives that reward the guiltiest and punish the
less guilty.
</P>
