$10,000 for each of dozens of souvenir booths, supplies and
services, but received nothing in return. Defendants include
Creative Travel Services, which also brought 3,000 teen-agers from
around the country to work at the kiosks, but then could neither
feed nor house them. (Croft, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   KING-PROFIT _ King family and Intellectual Property Management
Inc. control MLK's image and words. Now they've begun capitalizing
on it in a high-profile way, with a new video and CD, among other
products. We look at their plans, with a brief recap of how the two
groups became associated and the controversy that involved. Video
is released on Tuesday. (Harris, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20-25. WITH PHOTOS (Philip Jones of IPM).
</P>
<P>
   w/ KING-VIDEO _ Short review of the new animated video, ``Our
Friend Martin,'' with Angela Bassett, Whoopi Goldberg, et al. doing
voices. (Harris, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 8.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) general news and (l) Lifestyle categories.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-SPEAKER _ When the Texas House convenes on Tuesday, its
first order of business will be to elect a new speaker. But the
coronation occurred 18 months ago, when the House adjourned and
members immediately agreed that Speaker Pete Laney should get a
fourth term. Laney will be re-elected without opposition, despite
his pledge in 1993 to be a reform speaker who unlike his
predecessors would serve only one term. A look at the man and
office. (Greenberger, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   ATTENTION: Texas Editors
</P>
<P>
   w/TEXAS-LEGISBOX _ A rundown of the ceremony and schedule for
Tuesday, plus how to attend. (Greenberger/Elizondo, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-HIGHERED _ State Rep. Irma Rangel and others gather to
discuss higher education issues and the upcoming legislative
session in a first-ever symposium sponsored by the College Board
and other education groups. (Brooks, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   SCGAMBLE _ A new governor was swept into office largely on the
promise that education could be helped by a South Carolina state
lottery similar to Georgia's. But at the same time legislators
debate how to start such a plan, they also are arguing against
casino ships that have started plying the waters off the state's
coast. How are these conflicting views of gambling playing in the
Palmetto State? Also, the lottery debate here may be a presursor to
what may happen in Alabama and Tennessee as far as gambling. Pegged
to Jan. 12 opening of Legislature. (Manuel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DUANE-OWEN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Jury selection started this
week in the murder trial of Duane Owen, a chronic liar who has
confessed to murders in Florida and Colorado. This story chronicles
game of cat and mouse with detectives who have investigated his
stories. (Stapleton, Palm Beach Post). EDs: Mug of Owens available.
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ATTENTION: Florida, Colorado editors.
</P>
