<P>
   DIAMOND-CARTEL (Johannesburg, South Africa) _ A diamond cartel
is forever. Oppenheimers, nearly so. The cartel is De Beers, and De
Beers is the Oppenheimers _ for three generations, the most
important business figures in this country. But for Nicholas Frank
Oppenheimer, 53, who became chairman of De Beers a year ago, this
is not an easy time: Last month, the company announced that it had
sold fewer diamonds than it had for 12 years, a mere $3.4 billion
worth. But not to panic. This has happened before. By Donald G.
McNeil Jr.
</P>
