<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: PALER SHADES, TO CHASE WINTER 
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Color was the big message of the spring collections,
and bursts of sky blue, pink, yellow and lilac are now in stores to
add cheer to midwinter wardrobes.
</P>
<P>
   The rainbow at Macy's includes Emanuel/Emanuel Ungaro's pale
yellow suede jacket, $650; DKNY's floral-trimmed pale blue
cardigan, $115; Laundry by Shelli Segal's pale pink spaghetti-strap
silk dress with a matching cardigan sweater, $272; BCBG's
peasant-neck blouse in pale blue, $86; Anne Klein's seafoam
cardigan, $215, and tank, $135; Parallel's blue cardigan with white
embroidery, $176, and Nathalie M's satin mules in pale blue or
pink, $167.
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has a pale mauve cotton roll-neck sweater,
$200, and matching trousers, $265, from Kors by Michael Kors; a
silk-and-cotton blend shirt in pale blue or mauve, $175, from Ralph
by Ralph Lauren, and a blue cashmere V-neck sweater, $155, by
Theory.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
