<P>
   &UR; LEVI -  &LR; Peter Jacobi resigned as Levi Strauss &AMP; Co.'s president
and chief operating officer yesterday, saying a fresh perspective
is needed to turn around the ailing jeans-maker. By Carol Emert
</P>
<P>
   &UR; STREET &LR;  - Mark Veverka's investment column.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; YOUR MONEY PACKAGE &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; HIGHTECH -  &LR; Those astonishingly fast-moving high-technology stocks
had another great day yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   The tech-laden Nasdaq composite index hit its seventh-straight
record, jumping 40.18 points to 2,384.59. It has risen 68 percent
since hitting a 52-week low on October 8.
</P>
<P>
   That phenomenal streak has some market experts worrying that the
high-tech race car may be nearing the finish line. By Arthur M.
Louis
</P>
<P>
   &UR; EURO -  &LR; Castles, statues and mountain vistas may be on your
agenda this year if you're taking a vacation in Europe. One thing
you won't see, however, is the euro. By Carol Emert
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONEYBAG  &LR; - Question: I have several U.S. savings bonds that
are 12 years old and no longer drawing interest. I contacted two
banks, but they won't cash the bonds for me. What should I do?
Columnist Arthur M. Louis has the answer
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
