<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 1/11/98. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 11, 1999 -- IMPEACH-3, 1-11 -- Sen.
Mike DeWine (D-Ohio), third from left, discusses the Senate
impeachment proceedings with members of his staff on Monday. Two
days after the Senate struck an unexpected note of harmony with an
agreement on how to conduct the impeachment trial, Republicans and
Democrats clashed anew on Monday over whether to call witnesses.
(Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- Jan. 11, 1999 -- FBN-JETS-PARCELLS,
1-11 -- Bill Parcels, head coach of the New York Jets, speaks to
reporters on Monday. His team put on a powerful offensive show on
Sunday, and didn't allow several mental and physical blips to halt
them from defeating the Jaguars by 34-24 in what was the first
playoff game for more than half the Jets. It was also their seventh
straight victory. (Vic DeLucia/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) DETROIT -- Jan. 11, 1999 -- DETROIT-CLEANUP, 1-11 -- For
close to half a century, Detroit has had a policy of not plowing
residential streets. ``Out of my 50 years, it has never been
plowed,'' says James E. Barksdale, a 75-year-old retired auto parts
worker, of the street in front of his home on the city's east side.
When ice mixes with the snow, he cautions that ``you'd better use a
pick to get into it.'' (Peter Yates/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) NEW YORK -- Jan. 11, 1999 -- FAR-THEATER-REVIEW, 1-11 --
Michael Hayden and Lisa Emery in ``Far East,'' A.R. Gurney's uneven
but poignant new play at Lincoln Center. Throughout his career, the
author has been criticized for working on too small a canvas, but
here he tries hard to extend his thematic reach. (Sara Krulwich/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) NEW YORK -- Jan. 11, 1999 -- NY-PORN-APPEAL, 1-11 -- A
shop which only sold sexually explicit material gets rid of some of
its goods in order to make room for non-pornographic products
during a sale in June. The United States Supreme Court on Monday
refused to hear a challange to New York City Mayor Rudolph
Giuliani's administration in curbing sex shops in the city.
(William Lopez/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) LUBBOCK, Texas -- Jan. 11, 1999 -- PRAIRIE-DOG-DEBATE-2,
1-11 -- The U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service is set to announce soon
whether it sees sufficient cause for a nine-month study of whether
black-tailed prairie dogs, seen recently in a field, should be
listed as a threatened species. The notion of declaring the animals
threatened is greeted by most private ranchers and farmers in the
area with contempt. (David Bowser/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) AMARILLO, Texas -- Jan. 11, 1999 --
