<TEXT>
<P>
   The following story is being added to The New York Times front
page:
</P>
<P>
   EXCLUSIVE-BKN-JORDAN (New York) _ Michael Jordan, basketball's
pre-eminent player and the world's best known athlete, will retire
from the National Basketball Association for the second time in
five years, according to two officials in the NBA with knowledge of
Jordan's plans. They said on Monday night that they expected Jordan
to make an announcement this week, possibly as early as Wednesday,
at a news conference in Chicago. Story will move by 11 p.m., ET. By
Mike Wise.
</P>
</TEXT>
